text: Münster (Münster dialect: Mönster, Dutch: Munster, Frisian: Múnster, , () is the historical capital of Westphalia and belongs now to the state of North Rhine-Westphalia. About 270,000 people live there. There is an airport and a university. Münster was very powerful in the Middle Ages and the Renaissance. The Westphalian Peace was signed in Münster. == References == ==Other websites==
